# Narrative Architecture

These documents describe how Noeme is designed to work on the reader.

They are author-facing — not story content, but the logic behind 
how the story creates recognition, mystery, and emotional payoff.

| File | What it covers |
|---|---|
| 00_Bridge_Index | All recurring images, gestures, and connections between scenes |
| 01_Act_Emotional_Map | What the reader should feel at each stage |
| 02_Stretching_Concept | How mysteries expand without invalidating earlier understanding |
| 03_Visual_Motif_Bridges | Recurring visual patterns and what they carry |
| 04_Misdirection_Bridges | Where the reader is led toward a smaller explanation first |
| 05_Layered_Narrative_System | How different reader types experience the same scene differently |
| 06_Cosmology | Background architecture of the world |
